Text.Value: Much as I'd love to chat, I'm not allowed social breaks.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sarcasm. He's being forced to dig-- social breaks is a great understatement

Text.Value: As I supposed. If you'll excuse me, I have something terribly important to attend to.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sarcasm. He's attending to forced manual labor.

Text.Value: Because there are gnomes trapped behind these rocks, stuck with a drow.
These brutes are no mere goblins. I doubt you could take them on.
You won't find a worse gaggle of rare-do-wells than these 'Ironhand Gnomes' - except for Wulbren, desperate though his taste in companions might be.
I'm sensing a bit of history here.
What do you think will happen if the Ironhand Gnomes get their hands on runepowder?
Wander off alone and you might just meet them.
You were on a quest, weren't you? Making progress?
Actually - don't answer that. The littler said about it, the better.
Before you go - I do realise an amount of thanks are in order. You've helped me. Twice.
That is... not good news.
I'll keep you in my prayers.
Now - I do realise an amount of thanks are in order. You've helped me. Twice.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hesitating. He's been rude so far but does realize he owes you a debt.

Text.Value: I have no coin, but the foreman will be happy to provide.
This is no place to travel alone.
Leave.
We need to get them out - now.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC NODE - Halsin Talked of Moonrise

Text.Value: Do you know what the Ironhand Gnomes were doing down here?
Dig. And hope for an opportunity to escape.
I'm tempted to cheer at the sight of these dead duergar, but there are still gnomes trapped behind those rocks.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [DUPE] Stops digging and turns to address the Player <CodyM>

Text.Value: Do you know what Wulbren and the others were doing down here?
'Ironhand Gnomes'? Haven't heard of them.
There are still gnomes trapped behind those rocks - with a vicious cultist, no less.
First things first - you look exhausted. You should rest at my camp.
Sounds like you need my help again.
And so, you know - thank you. With that, I believe our business is concluded.
*He's lying...*

EditorData.NodeContext: Hi Milly! <3 Might be funny if it's slightly a little knowing sing-song

Text.Value: 'Hope', is it? Enjoy the rest of your life as a captive, then.
Ahem... that is... what do you know about runepowder?
The Towers must be close. And finding Moonrise means finding answers.
Certainly not! In case you haven't been paying attention, my friend has been taken captive. He needs me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Said with sarcasm. He loves wulbren.

Text.Value: I shouldn't be surprised, considering our history. And yet...

EditorData.logicalname: Didn't talk to barcus earlier, acknowledgin windmill

Text.Value: Not now - we need to clear the cave-in!
Ta!
Your friends are lost - there's no point dying for them.
Right. Ever the pragmatist, hm?
Their fight has little to do with freedom and everything to do with power. I told Wulbren not to go near them, but did he listen? He did not.
No.
I don't have time for this - the Ironhand Gnomes might already have their hands on runepowder!
Hm.

EditorData.logicalname: Didnt Talk to Beldron + Thulla quest

Text.Value: I could. But I probably won't.
I did. But not out of the kindness of my heart.
If Wulbren's dead, it's my job to find out who, when, where, and why.
How did you get captured?
Unfortunately, it didn't account for an army of mad Underdark cultists.
Moonrise? We're closing in on the Towers. And the curse...

EditorData.NodeContext: Forced levity - a side-glance at the player referencing that we're actually here to kill Nere, not save him.

Text.Value: Moonrise? We're nearing the Towers. We're nearing answers.

EditorData.NodeContext: Plainly stated, as if it's obvious. We're here to kill Nere, but Thrinn thinks we're here to save him. The player likely wants to keep it secret, but Lae'zel doesn't get subterfuge.

Text.Value: Hmm.
Leave.
As you know some of the Ironhand Gnomes - my friend Wulbren among them - have been taken prisoner in Moonrise Towers.
But! I was too late. Wulbren had already been taken to Moonrise Towers. The rest, put to work.

EditorData.NodeContext: Gestures with head to his surrounding gnomes. Said with bitterness; he doesn't like these lads

Text.Value: Realistically, your friend is probably already dead.
Barcus has the right idea. We've got to get to Moonrise too - and soon.
You're free - go on.
Probe his mind.
Why don't you rest in my camp before your next big move?
And so... to Moonrise Towers I go.
Won't be needing it, thank you!
How gallant. Don't suffocate on your way out, hmm?
And, erm, well... thank you.
Presumptuous. I'll get you out of here.
I suppose I do. Though I'm not counting on one of you to help one of me.
Moonrise? There's a lot resting on what we find in that place. It had better deliver.

EditorData.NodeContext: Discreet reference to Nere, whose head we're to collect as a bounty.

Text.Value: Looks like you need rescuing. Again.
Sounds like you made a profound tactical error.
Nothing good happens in the Underdark - you should know as well as I.
Nothing good happens in the Underdark.
I thought they'd be easy to outwit. I had an entire plan...
As I was contemplating his folly, I was spotted by a very ugly duergar.
Well. You... did it!
Nor did I account for some captives to be trapped in with the drow after the cave-in.
I'll keep them in my prayers.
Good bye, my misery's favourite companion.
I know someone of your background would fit right in in that heart of horrors, but for others of us it's quite a frightening prospect.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: No cinematics, here for logic purposes only

Text.Value: They call themselves 'freedom fighters'. I call them extremists.
Suit yourself.
That sounds like a challenge. I'll take care of your captors, and I'll get you out of here.
How did you end up here?
It isn't personal. No one likes the Ironhand Gnomes except the Ironhand Gnomes.
Don't sound so surprised.
What?!
And. Erm. Thank you.
What are the Ironhands doing down here? I thought their fight for gnomish freedom was local to Baldur's Gate.
Ironhand Gnomes... I recognise the name. They fight for gnomish recognition in the city, right?
I suspect I'll be rescuing you a third time, then.
I came down here looking for Wulbren - I suspected he and his little friends might've come to this region, and I was right.
Please. They get very aggressive if we stop digging.
They're not even going after him. I wish I were surprised.
Moonrise. We're getting close to the lion's den - and plenty of questions I have for the lion, too.
Now, I dig. It isn't good.
Why are you digging?
Ah. It's you. The mascot of my ill fortunes.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [DUPE] Stops digging and turns to address the Player <CodyM>

Text.Value: You will? If you are successful, that would be most convenient.

EditorData.NodeContext: A flash of excitement, then quick containment.

Text.Value: Erm - no offence.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: No cinematics, here for logic purposes only

Text.Value: Fine. Show me where to go, and I'll try my luck. I'll have a better chance of rescuing Wulbren if I'm at my best.
Free. Yes.
You could just ask for my help.
I won't leave them to his whims.
Thank you, but I doubt the gods will hear you down here.
I always do.
I must speak with Wulbren. Now more urgently than ever.
Help would be welcome. Whether you're up to the job remains to be seen.
Ah. It's you. The mascot of my ill fortunes...

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Barcus] Stops digging and turns to address the Player <CodyM>

Text.Value: Once again, however, you've done me a decent turn. Most amusing, watching you wallop greylings.
Leave.
A brave act. Your stature belies your courage.
Hiding in plain sight. A cunning strategy.
That was brave of you.
What's the next part of your plan?
I've learned that Wulbren and the others are in search of runepowder.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: MAde impossible per GUS-181625 - might bring htis back later if it feels like hter'es no chance to tell Barcus about it, but doesn't fit now

Text.Value: The duergar are dead. You need to run.
Pah. I was unlucky twice. The odds of it happening again are very slim.
No one should touch the stuff. Not Wulbren, and especially not those Ironhand jackals.
I thought I was.
You - get out of my nut! THIS MINUTE!
They're a clan of artificers in Baldur's Gate. I won't speak ill of their skills, but their politics are another matter entirely.
Farewell, Barcus - I wish you luck with your search.
How kind. Don't suffocate on your way out, hmm?
Rest at a drow camp? I'd be safer among mind flayers.
Rest at a duergar camp? I'd be safer among mind flayers.
I don't know if you heard, but some of the Ironhand Gnomes - my friend Wulbren among them - have been taken prisoner in Moonrise Towers.
... then again, a small rest might be prudent. Give me time to think.
I believe I'm destined for the Towers as well. I'll look for your friends.
Friend. Singular. I'm looking for Wulbren - if anyone else should be incidentally helped, then bully for them.

EditorData.NodeContext: Emphasis on 'FrienD'. Bitterness toward other guy

Text.Value: Too many permutations. Quite the headache.

Synopsis: If you saved Barcus from the windmill, you can meet him again in the underdark. He's been captured once again - this time by a band of duergar (who follow the Absolute, same as the goblins did previously). If you get rid of his captors, you can talk to him some more about his next steps. He's still keen on saving his friend, Wulbren.
